						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotewrapper"><div class="quotetitle">Emerson wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">It sounds like a fancy way of spinning the fact that the image is least distorted near the middle, heh.</div></div><br /><br />Yep.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_e_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" />  It really is a good effect, though, since it lets you get away with using fewer pixels in the periphery.  It looks much, much better than a non-compressed resolution of 640x800 would appear at 90 degrees.  If you wanted to be really fancy, you could do variable rendering with higher detail in the center of the image, but the returns on that will not be useful till we have much higher resolution.</div>

